Creating Measures for KPIs and Graphs 11 1. Setup: Begin by accessing the 'hr_attrition_dataset' and 'employee_attrition_predictions' in Power BI to start crafting measures that will drive insights in KPIs and graphical representations.

2. Dataset Selection: Choose the dataset where you intend to create new measures. Begin with the 'hr_attrition_dataset' to establish a foundation for comprehensive analysis.

3. Begin Measure Creation: Click 'New Measure' within your selected dataset to open the formula input area. This is where you will define the metrics for your analysis.

4. Implement DAX Formulas: Carefully input the DAX formulas that represent the metrics you wish to analyze. These will be utilized in both KPIs and various graphs within your dashboard.

5. Apply to Predictive Analysis: Replicate the measure creation steps in the 'employee_attrition_predictions' dataset to maintain analytic consistency and depth.

Measure Categories for KPIs and Graphs:

6. Main KPI Measures -
Overview: Central metrics pivotal for KPI cards, changing based on user selections to highlight critical data insights.
KPI TotalEmployees = COUNTROWS(hr_attrition_dataset)

KPI Attrition = IF(    ISBLANK(        DIVIDE(            CALCULATE(COUNTROWS('hr_attrition_dataset'), 'hr_attrition_dataset'[Left] = 1),            COUNTROWS('hr_attrition_dataset')        )    ),    0,    ROUND(        DIVIDE(            CALCULATE(COUNTROWS('hr_attrition_dataset'), 'hr_attrition_dataset'[Left] = 1),            COUNTROWS('hr_attrition_dataset')        ) * 100,        0    ) / 100)

KPI Satisfaction = ROUND(        AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[satisfaction_level]) * 100,        0    ) / 100

KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany = AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[time_spend_company])

KPI_AvgMonthlyHrs = AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[average_montly_hours])

7. Left KPI Measures-
Overview: Metrics that remain constant to serve as a baseline, allowing for comparative analysis against dynamic selections.
L_Sub KPI_EmployeesTotal = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),  // Check if the specific column is being filtered    DIVIDE(        [KPI TotalEmployees],         [Meas TotalEmployee],         BLANK()      ),    " " )

L_Sub KPI_Attrition = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),    ROUND(        CALCULATE(            AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[Left]),            ALL(hr_attrition_dataset)        ) * 100,        0    ) / 100,    " ")

L_Sub KPI_Satisfaction = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),    ROUND(        CALCULATE(            [KPI_Satisfaction],            ALL(hr_attrition_dataset)        ) * 100,        0    ) / 100,    " ")

L_Sub KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),    CALCULATE(        AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[time_spend_company]),        ALL(hr_attrition_dataset)     ),    " " )

L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),    CALCULATE(        AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[average_montly_hours]),        ALL(hr_attrition_dataset)    ),    " " )

8. Right KPI Measures -
Overview: Calculated metrics showing percentage changes or trends, offering insight into shifts and patterns relative to the main and left KPIs.

R_Sub KPI_Attrition = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),     DIVIDE(        [KPI Attrition] - [L_Sub KPI_Attrition],         [L_Sub KPI_Attrition],        BLANK()     ),     " " )

R_Sub KPI_Satisfaction = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),     DIVIDE(        [KPI Satisfaction] - [L_Sub KPI_Satisfaction],         [L_Sub KPI_Satisfaction],        BLANK()     ),    " ")

R_Sub KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),     DIVIDE(        ROUND([KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany], 0) - ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany], 0),         ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany], 0),        BLANK()     ),     " " )

R_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),     IF(        DIVIDE(ROUND([KPI_AvgMonthlyHrs], 0) - ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0), ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0)) > 0,        MAX(            CEILING(                DIVIDE(ROUND([KPI_AvgMonthlyHrs], 0) - ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0), ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0)),                0.01            ),            0.01        ),        IF(            DIVIDE(ROUND([KPI_AvgMonthlyHrs], 0) - ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0), ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0)) < 0,            MIN(                FLOOR(                    DIVIDE(ROUND([KPI_AvgMonthlyHrs], 0) - ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0), ROUND([L_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours], 0)),                    -0.01                ),                -0.01            ),            0        )    ),    " " )

9.  Indicator KPI Measures -
Overview: Directional indicators derived from right KPI measures, illustrating upward or downward trends for quick visual guidance.

Ind Attrition = SWITCH(    TRUE(),    [R_Sub KPI_Attrition] = " ", " ",     [R_Sub KPI_Attrition] > 0, UNICHAR(9650),     [R_Sub KPI_Attrition] < 0, UNICHAR(9660)," " )

Ind_KPI Satisfaction = SWITCH(    TRUE(),    [R_Sub KPI_Satisfaction] = " ", " ",     [R_Sub KPI_Satisfaction] > 0, UNICHAR(9650),     [R_Sub KPI_Satisfaction] < 0, UNICHAR(9660),      " " )

Ind_AvgTimeSpendCompany = SWITCH(    TRUE(),    [R_Sub KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany] = " ", " ",     [R_Sub KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany] > 0, UNICHAR(9650),     [R_Sub KPI_AvgTimeSpendCompany] < 0, UNICHAR(9660),      " " )

Ind_AvgMonthlyHrs = SWITCH(    TRUE(),    [R_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours] = " ", " ",     [R_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours] > 0, UNICHAR(9650),     [R_Sub KPI_AvgMonthlyhours] < 0, UNICHAR(9660),      " " )

10. Measures for Graphs:
Overview - Additional metrics not specifically tied to KPIs but essential for detailed graph-based analyses. These measures enrich the dashboard's narrative by providing broader context and deeper insights.

Attrition % = DIVIDE(    CALCULATE(        COUNTROWS(hr_attrition_dataset),         hr_attrition_dataset[Left] = 1    ),     CALCULATE(        COUNTROWS(hr_attrition_dataset),        ALL(hr_attrition_dataset[number_project])    )) + 0.0001 // Adding a small number

Avg Monthly Hrs = AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[average_montly_hours])

Satisfaction % = AVERAGE(hr_attrition_dataset[satisfaction_level])

Meas TotalEmployee = IF(    ISCROSSFILTERED(hr_attrition_dataset[FilterCheck]),    CALCULATE(        COUNTROWS(hr_attrition_dataset),        ALL(hr_attrition_dataset)    ),    " ")
